<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    Stop the "Supply Balloons" event from ever being rolled.

    "Supply Balloons" is Medieval Fantasy Themed Relic Quests' reskin (letter label + text) of the
    vanilla ResourcePodCrash incident - a free-loot event where cargo pods crash near the colony.
    The storyteller fires it through its Misc-category roll (StorytellerCompProperties_CategoryMTB,
    category Misc), where each incident competes by its baseChance. Setting ResourcePodCrash's
    baseChance to 0 drops it out of that weighted pool, so it is never selected, while leaving every
    other Misc incident untouched.

    This edits the Core incident directly, so it is global (no storyteller ever rolls it), not scoped
    to The Antagonist - there is no clean way to exclude one incident from a category per storyteller.
    Reward/gift deliveries that use drop pods are a separate mechanism and are unaffected.
-->
<Patch>
    <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
        <xpath>Defs/IncidentDef[defName="ResourcePodCrash"]/baseChance</xpath>
        <value>
            <baseChance>0</baseChance>
        </value>
    </Operation>
</Patch>
